Small talk in Spanish When I was a junior in university way back in 2004, I went for a semester abroad at la Universidad Complutense de Madrid in Spain.&nbsp;
Since I grew up talking to my abuelitos in Chile on the phone, I figured I was fluent enough to make friends with my new Spanish classmates.&nbsp;
You can imagine my shock on the first day of school. I walked up to twenty students at the classroom door and totally froze.

